#compdef graphql-codegen gql-gen graphql-code-generator graphql-codegen-esm graphql-codegen-cjs
# ============================================================================
# graphql-codegen - generate code from
#                    GraphQL schemas
#                    (TypeScript/Node, MIT)
#
# Author : Dotan Simha + The Guild
#           (theguild.dev; the canonical
#           GraphQL ecosystem
#           organization)
# Upstream: https://github.com/dotansimha/graphql-code-generator
#           (new home: https://github.com/
#           the-guild-org/graphql-code-
#           generator)
# npm pkg : @graphql-codegen/cli
#
# `graphql-codegen` is The Guild's
# canonical Node CLI for generating typed
# client + server code from GraphQL
# schemas. The most-installed GraphQL
# tooling package in the Node ecosystem
# alongside graphql-js + apollo-client.
#
# Architecture:
#   1. **Schema introspection** (load
#      GraphQL schemas from URLs + files
#      + git repos + GraphQL Hive
#      registry)
#   2. **Plugin-based generation**
#      (~100+ official plugins for
#      TypeScript + React + Vue + Apollo
#      + URQL + Relay + many more)
#   3. **Watch mode** (--watch for
#      development workflows; rebuilds
#      on schema changes)
#   4. **Multiple output targets**
#      (single config can generate to
#      multiple files for different
#      audiences - server types +
#      client hooks + mock data)
#
# Distinguishing features:
#   - **THE canonical GraphQL codegen
#     tool** (~10M+ weekly npm downloads
#     across @graphql-codegen/* family;
#     no other GraphQL codegen tool
#     comes close to adoption)
#   - **Plugin ecosystem** (~100+
#     official plugins + many community
#     plugins; comprehensive coverage
#     of GraphQL client + server
#     codegen needs)
#   - **The Guild stewardship**
#     (canonical GraphQL ecosystem
#     organization)
#   - **Multi-framework support**
#     (Apollo Client + URQL + Relay +
#     SWR + React Query + Vue Apollo +
#     ...)
#   - **Type-safety guarantees**
#     (generated TypeScript types match
#     schema exactly)
#
# Generated outputs:
#   - **TypeScript types** for schema
#     types + custom scalars + enums
#   - **Operation types** (typed
#     Query/Mutation/Subscription
#     types from .graphql query
#     documents)
#   - **React hooks** (typed Apollo
#     useQuery/useMutation/
#     useSubscription hooks)
#   - **URQL hooks** + **Relay hooks**
#     + **SWR hooks**
#   - **Server resolver types** (typed
#     Resolver function signatures for
#     graphql-js + Apollo Server +
#     GraphQL Yoga + Nexus)
#   - **Document AST** (compiled
#     operation documents for runtime
#     dispatch)
#   - **Mock data** (typed mock data
#     generators for testing)
#
# Use cases:
#   - **TypeScript + GraphQL client**
#     (generate typed Apollo
#     useQuery/useMutation hooks from
#     .graphql files)
#   - **GraphQL server type
#     generation** (generate typed
#     resolver function signatures for
#     graphql-js/Apollo Server)
#   - **Multi-team codegen** (single
#     config.yml generates client +
#     server + admin tool types from
#     same schema)
#   - **CI/CD type checking** (--check
#     mode validates that generated
#     types are up-to-date)
#
# Usage:
#   graphql-codegen [options]
#
# Flags:
#   -c, --config <file>            - path
#                                     to
#                                     config
#                                     file
#                                     (default:
#                                     codegen
#                                     .yml or
#                                     .ts or
#                                     .json)
#   -w, --watch                    - watch
#                                     for
#                                     schema
#                                     +
#                                     operation
#                                     changes
#                                     +
#                                     regenerate
#   -s, --silent                   - silent
#                                     mode
#                                     (only
#                                     show
#                                     errors)
#   -e, --errors-only              - only
#                                     show
#                                     errors
#                                     (still
#                                     emit
#                                     output)
#   -r, --require <module>         - require
#                                     module
#                                     before
#                                     execution
#                                     (e.g.
#                                     dotenv/
#                                     config)
#   -o, --overwrite                - overwrite
#                                     existing
#                                     files
#                                     (default
#                                     behavior;
#                                     opposite
#                                     is
#                                     --no-
#                                     overwrite)
#   -p, --project <name>           - specific
#                                     project
#                                     name
#                                     (when
#                                     multi-
#                                     project
#                                     config)
#       --profile                  - enable
#                                     CPU
#                                     profiling
#                                     (developer
#                                     workflow)
#       --check                    - check if
#                                     files
#                                     are up-
#                                     to-date
#                                     (exit
#                                     non-
#                                     zero if
#                                     not;
#                                     useful
#                                     for CI)
#       --verbose                  - verbose
#                                     logging
#       --debug                    - debug
#                                     logging
#   -h, --help                     - show
#                                     help
#   -v, --version                  - show
#                                     version
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Generate code from default
#   # codegen.yml
#   graphql-codegen
#
#   # Watch mode for development
#   graphql-codegen --watch
#
#   # Custom config file
#   graphql-codegen --config codegen.ts
#
#   # Check generated files are
#   # up-to-date (CI/CD use)
#   graphql-codegen --check
#
#   # Specific project in multi-project
#   # config
#   graphql-codegen --project frontend
#
#   # Verbose output for debugging
#   graphql-codegen --verbose --debug
#
#   # Silent mode (CI logs)
#   graphql-codegen --silent
#
#   # Require dotenv before execution
#   graphql-codegen \
#     --require dotenv/config \
#     --config codegen.ts
#
# Configuration file (codegen.ts):
#   ```typescript
#   import type { CodegenConfig } from
#     '@graphql-codegen/cli';
#
#   const config: CodegenConfig = {
#     schema: 'https://api.example.com/graphql',
#     documents: ['src/**/*.graphql'],
#     ignoreNoDocuments: true,
#     generates: {
#       './src/gql/': {
#         preset: 'client',
#         plugins: [],
#         config: {
#           useTypeImports: true,
#           skipTypename: false,
#         }
#       },
#       './src/gql/schema.d.ts': {
#         plugins: ['typescript', 'typescript-resolvers'],
#         config: {
#           useIndexSignature: true,
#           contextType: '../context#MyContext',
#         }
#       }
#     }
#   };
#
#   export default config;
#   ```
#
# Or as YAML (codegen.yml):
#   ```yaml
#   schema: https://api.example.com/graphql
#   documents:
#     - src/**/*.graphql
#   generates:
#     ./src/gql/index.ts:
#       plugins:
#         - typescript
#         - typescript-operations
#         - typescript-react-apollo
#       config:
#         withHooks: true
#         withComponent: false
#   ```
#
# Popular plugin packages (install
# separately):
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript           - TypeScript
#                                             types
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-operations - Operation
#                                             types
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-react-apollo - Apollo
#                                             hooks
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-urql      - URQL
#                                             hooks
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-resolvers - Server
#                                             resolver
#                                             types
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-mongodb   - MongoDB
#                                             schemas
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-graphql-files-modules
#                                         - .graphql
#                                             file
#                                             modules
#   @graphql-codegen/typescript-react-query - React
#                                             Query
#                                             hooks
#   @graphql-codegen/client-preset        - Modern
#                                             client
#                                             preset
#                                             (replaces
#                                             many
#                                             individual
#                                             plugins)
#
# Binary aliases (all run the same CLI):
#   gql-gen                        - shorter
#                                     alias
#   graphql-codegen                - primary
#                                     name
#   graphql-code-generator         - full
#                                     name
#   graphql-codegen-esm            - ESM
#                                     variant
#   graphql-codegen-cjs            - CJS
#                                     variant
#
# The graphql/graphql-js lane is built
# on `graphql` (the canonical Node
# GraphQL reference implementation by
# Meta/Facebook), imported via the
# @graphql-codegen/core + plugin packages
# for schema parsing + validation +
# introspection.
#
# graphql/graphql-js is the de-facto
# canonical Node GraphQL library:
#   - **THE GraphQL reference
#     implementation** (created by
#     Facebook 2015 alongside the
#     GraphQL spec; the implementation
#     that defines what GraphQL means
#     for JavaScript)
#   - **Spec-defining role** (changes
#     to graphql-js often inform
#     evolution of the GraphQL spec
#     itself)
#   - **Pure JavaScript implementation**
#     (no native bindings; runs in Node
#     + browsers + Deno + Bun)
#   - **Schema construction** (both
#     code-first via GraphQLObjectType +
#     schema-first via buildSchema from
#     SDL)
#   - **Query parsing + validation +
#     execution** (the complete
#     GraphQL pipeline)
#   - **Subscription support** (the
#     AsyncIterable-based subscription
#     primitive)
#   - **~30,000,000 weekly npm downloads
#     as `graphql` package**
#     (foundational dependency of
#     every Node GraphQL tool)
#   - **20,000+ stars on github.com/
#     graphql/graphql-js**
#
